         <abstract>
            <p>A tabular, recursive method is presented for the computation of a sequence of abscissae designed to converge to a simple zero of an analytic function. The key to the method is an efficient means for evaluating the zeros of a sequence of rational functions, having linear numerators, fitted to information previously computed. Regional and asymptotic convergence properties of the method are described. Conditions sufficient to ensure convergence are derived, and it is shown that asymptotically quadratic convergence can be achieved, at the cost of  only a moderate amount of "overhead" computation.</p>
          </abstract>
